review_blob: Pours a dark brown with nice creamy off white head that goes flat quickly. Aromas of caramel and smoked malts. Nice full robust soft mouthfeel. Caramel malt follows through in the mouth, with lovely long lingering aftertaste. Loved this.

Fresh aroma of citrus fruit nice head when poured. Pale amber colour. Nice fresh flavours in the mouth and hint of malty sweetness on the end.  Overall a nice easy going introduction style of IPA but lacks deppth of more craft IPAs
beer_name: Monteiths Brewers Series India Pale Ale
